    <text id="A1429T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Nelson Hotchkiss and W. B. Young promise to pay Mrs. Robberts in a year for the
                    use of three servants.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>$ 700. On the 25 day of December 1864 we or either of us Bind ourselves our heirs
                    &amp; co to pay to Mrs. <del hand="h1">Betsy</del>Polly <add hand="h1"
                        place="inline">
                        <unclear>W</unclear>
                    </add> &amp; Robberts Seven Hundred Dollars for the hire of two servant men
                    &amp; one woman names as follows. Woodson , George &amp; Jenna - - - .
                    This year and to furnish them with the usual amounts of clothing except Blankets</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Witness our hands &amp; seal this 28<hi rend="super">th</hi>
                        <orig reg="day">Dday</orig> December 1863</salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="Nelson">N.</abbr> H. Hotchkiss (Seal)<lb/> W B Young (Seal)</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">If the above Servants are rehired Mrs Robberts is to have
                        the <orig reg="privilege">privalege</orig> of hiring them or finding them
                        places. <abbr expan="Nelson">N.</abbr> H. Hotchkiss</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
